%N A116036 Numbers k such that k + prime(k) + prime(prime(k)) is a prime, where prime(k) denotes the k-th prime.
%H A116036 Robert Israel, <a href="/A116036/b116036.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A116036 7 + prime(7) + prime(prime(7)) = 83 (prime).
%p A116036 filter:= proc(n) local p; p:= ithprime(n); isprime(n+p+ithprime(p)) end proc:
%p A116036 select(filter, [seq(i,i=1..1000,2)]); # _Robert Israel_, Apr 30 2026
